9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 380, L.D. 612, “An Act to Require the
10 Department of Health and Human Services to Review Medicaid, Supplemental Nutrition
11 Assistance Program and Electronic Benefits Transfer Card Transactions and Lottery
12 Operations”
13 Amend the bill by striking out the title and substituting the following:
14 'An Act to Require the Department of Health and Human Services to Review
15 Electronic Benefits Transfer Card Transactions'
16 Amend the bill by striking out all of section 1.
17 Amend the bill in section 2 in subsection 1-A in the 2nd line (page 2, line 15 in L.D.)
18 by inserting after the following: "out-of-state" the following: 'swiped'
19 Amend the bill in section 2 in subsection 1-A in the 3rd line (page 2, line 16 in L.D.)
20 by striking out the following: "90" and inserting the following: '45'
21 Amend the bill in section 2 in subsection 1-A in the 3rd line (page 2, line 16 in L.D.)
22 by inserting after the following: "recipient's" the following: 'swiped'
23 Amend the bill in section 2 in subsection 1-A in the 4th line (page 2, line 17 in L.D.)
24 by inserting after the following: "out-of-state" the following: 'swiped'
25 Amend the bill in section 2 in subsection 1-A in the 5th line (page 2, line 18 in L.D.)
26 by striking out the following: "90" and inserting the following: '45'
27 Amend the bill in section 2 in subsection 1-A in the last line (page 2, line 24 in L.D.)
28 by inserting after the following: "State." the following: 'The department shall exclude
29 swiped EBT card transactions made in the State of New Hampshire from the requirements
30 of this subsection. For the purposes of this subsection, "swiped EBT card transaction"
31 means a transaction that requires the user to insert or present an EBT card into or to a
32 physical card reading device to complete the transaction.'
33 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
34 number to read consecutively.
